  "body": "This PR adds the [QtWayland](https://doc.qt.io/qt-5/wayland-and-qt.html) module into the `qt` package in depends.\r\n\r\nThis change allows to build release binaries for Linux systems that can run natively\u2014as a Wayland client\u2014on modern desktops with Wayland compositors.\r\n\r\nCloses #19950.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nThe diff for Qt \"Configure summary\" in depends:\r\n```diff\r\n@@ -73,14 +73,14 @@\r\n       Using system libjpeg ............... no\r\n     PNG .................................. yes\r\n       Using system libpng ................ no\r\n-  EGL .................................... no\r\n+  EGL .................................... yes\r\n   OpenVG ................................. no\r\n   OpenGL:\r\n     Desktop OpenGL ....................... no\r\n-    OpenGL ES 2.0 ........................ no\r\n-    OpenGL ES 3.0 ........................ no\r\n-    OpenGL ES 3.1 ........................ no\r\n-    OpenGL ES 3.2 ........................ no\r\n+    OpenGL ES 2.0 ........................ yes\r\n+    OpenGL ES 3.0 ........................ yes\r\n+    OpenGL ES 3.1 ........................ yes\r\n+    OpenGL ES 3.2 ........................ yes\r\n   Vulkan ................................. no\r\n   Session Management ..................... no\r\n Features used by QPA backends:\r\n@@ -130,6 +130,20 @@\r\n   Tester for item models ................. yes\r\n Qt Tools:\r\n   QDoc ................................... no\r\n+Qt Wayland Drivers:\r\n+  EGL .................................... yes\r\n+  Raspberry Pi ........................... no\r\n+  XComposite EGL ......................... no\r\n+  XComposite GLX ......................... no\r\n+  DRM EGL ................................ yes\r\n+  libhybris EGL .......................... no\r\n+  Linux dma-buf server buffer integration . no\r\n+  Vulkan-based server buffer integration . no\r\n+  Shm emulation server buffer integration . yes\r\n+Qt Wayland Client ........................ yes\r\n+Qt Wayland Compositor .................... yes\r\n+Qt Wayland Compositor Layer Plugins:\r\n+  VSP2 hardware layer integration ........ no\r\n \r\n Note: Also available for Linux: linux-clang linux-icc\r\n \r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nHere is an excerpt from the log on Fedora 34 + GNOME:\r\n```\r\n$ QT_QPA_PLATFORM=wayland ./bitcoin-qt -printtoconsole\r\nWarning: Ignoring XDG_SESSION_TYPE=wayland on Gnome. Use QT_QPA_PLATFORM=wayland to run on Wayland anyway.\r\n2021-08-15T16:04:53Z Bitcoin Core version v22.99.0-1833ecbe1307-dirty (release build)\r\n2021-08-15T16:04:53Z Qt 5.12.11 (static), plugin=wayland (static)\r\n2021-08-15T16:04:53Z Static plugins:\r\n2021-08-15T16:04:53Z  QXcbIntegrationPlugin, version 330752\r\n2021-08-15T16:04:53Z  QWaylandIntegrationPlugin, version 330752\r\n2021-08-15T16:04:53Z  QWaylandEglClientBufferPlugin, version 330752\r\n2021-08-15T16:04:53Z  QWaylandBradientDecorationPlugin, version 330752\r\n2021-08-15T16:04:53Z  QWaylandXdgShellIntegrationPlugin, version 330752\r\n2021-08-15T16:04:53Z Style: fusion / QFusionStyle\r\n2021-08-15T16:04:53Z System: Fedora 34 (Workstation Edition), x86_64-little_endian-lp6\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nGuix builds are not possible for now.",
